{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bfb36764-96b2-46d0-bc56-cd834cb07f94","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove this line -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n   MSTest.Sdk 3.8+ defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is absent/false.\n\n2. **Run tests** with `dotnet test` as usual — no other changes needed. The SDK wires up the new platform automatically.\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n- CLI output format changes slightly.\n- Some VSTest-specific `.runsettings` options may not apply. Check for warnings.\n- If you use `dotnet test --filter`, the filter syntax remains the same.\n- Extensions like code coverage or TRX reporting may need their Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents (e.g., `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"423c7dcc-f02b-4f7e-8c18-dae6f086c101","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project that uses MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration, not a code change in a specific repository. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":322,"requestId":"BD0E:7818E:1D9BF3A:214C8C6:6A07C4CC"},"id":"278550fb-ca14-49c4-b3ca-605190dbac68","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:13:57.129Z","parentId":"ea06657d-35be-4bd0-a15b-90f7d3693990"}
